Here is a simple VBA script for Excel that accepts the English name of one of the colors of the rainbow and sets the cell that contains that value to that background color.

```vba
Sub SetRainbowColor()
    
    Dim ws As Worksheet
    Dim cell As Range
    Dim colorName As String
    
    Set ws = ThisWorkbook.Worksheets("Sheet1") ' Replace Sheet1 with the name of your sheet
    
    colorName = InputBox("Please enter the color name (English) of the rainbow: ")
    
    For Each cell In ws.UsedRange
        If LCase(cell.Value) = LCase(colorName) Then
            Select Case LCase(colorName)
                Case "red"
                    cell.Interior.Color = RGB(255, 0, 0)
                Case "orange"
                    cell.Interior.Color = RGB(255, 165, 0)
                Case "yellow"
                    cell.Interior.Color = RGB(255, 255, 0)
                Case "green"
                    cell.Interior.Color = RGB(0, 128, 0)
                Case "blue"
                    cell.Interior.Color = RGB(0, 0, 255)
                Case "indigo"
                    cell.Interior.Color = RGB(75, 0, 130)
                Case "violet"
                    cell.Interior.Color = RGB(148, 0, 211)
                Case Else
                    MsgBox "Invalid color name. Please enter a color of the rainbow.", vbExclamation, "Invalid Color"
                    Exit Sub
            End Select
        End If
    Next cell

    MsgBox "Color applied successfully.", vbInformation, "Success"

End Sub
```

To run this script:

1. Open your Excel workbook and press `Alt + F11` to open the Visual Basic for Applications (VBA) editor
2. Go to `Insert > Module` to insert a new module
3. Copy and paste the code above into the newly created module
4. Close the VBA editor by clicking the `X` button or pressing `Alt + Q`
5. Press `Alt + F8` to open the "Macro" dialog box, select `SetRainbowColor`, and click the "Run" button
6. Enter the English name of one of the colors of the rainbow when prompted, and then click "OK"

The script will search the sheet for the specified color name and set the background color of the cell accordingly.